Taiwan Stocks: Formosa International, Foxconn Technology, HTC

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-06-13T06:16:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/acer-au-optronics-china-airlines-tsmc-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Taiwan  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1:30 p.m. in Taipei trading.  The Taiex Index fell 124.87, or 1.4 percent, to 8,712.95,
closing at the lowest level since April 19. The measure
retreated for a fourth straight day, the longest stretch of
losses since March 15.  Tourism-related shares:  Formosa International Hotels Corp. (2707) 
(2707 TT) advanced 2.1 percent to NT$541.  Ambassador Hotel (2704)  Ltd.
(2704 TT) gained 0.6 percent to NT$46.05.  China  and Taiwan will
start a pilot travel program on June 28 allowing mainland
Chinese from selected cities to visit Taiwan as individuals, the
official Xinhua News Agency reported.  EVA Airways Corp. (2618)  (2618 TT) lost 2.9 percent to NT$27.25,
the lowest close since May 5. The island’s second-largest
carrier was cut to “neutral” from “outperform” at Credit
Suisse Group AG.  Foxconn Technology Co. (2354 TT) slumped 6.9 percent to
NT$121.50, the lowest close since April 15, after the company
said sales slumped 53 percent in May to NT$3.85 billion ($134
million) from a year earlier. The company was also lowered to
“neutral” from “add” at Fubon Securities Co. by equity
analyst Jeff Pu.  HTC Corp. (2498)  (2498 TT) sank 6.9 percent to NT$1,085, the
lowest close since March 29. UBS AG said in a report the company
cut around 1 million units of orders across different models in
the third quarter. Daiwa Securities Capital Markets Co. wrote in
a report the company lowered its component procurement needs for
the second and third quarter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Weiyi Lim in Singapore at 
 wlim26@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net . 